OL,3,C'From wheelie bins to overhanging
OL,4,Chedges - there're so many difficult
OL,5,Cobstacles'
OL,7,FA man from Tilehurst, Reading, says
OL,8,Fhis life is becoming increasingly
OL,9,Fdifficult because of obstacles on the
OL,10,Fpavements.
OL,12,FStuart Pearce relies on his guide dog,
OL,13,FOlivia, to steer him round any objects
OL,14,Fin his path but negotiating his way
OL,15,Falong the pavements can be challenging.
OL,17,FThe Guide Dogs charity says pavement
OL,18,Fhazards are an increasing problem,
OL,19,Fparticularly in towns and cities. Cars
OL,20,Fparked on the pavement can pose one of
OL,21,Fthe biggest problems.
